            "body": "<p>call getItem() on the ItemEvent that is passed to your ItemListener<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 12719275,
            "question_id": 12719243
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/PZSHL.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 939255,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 967638,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/967638/amarnath",
                "reputation": 8895,
                "display_name": "Amarnath",
                "accept_rate": 98
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1349315613,
            "creation_date": 1349315613,
            "body": "<p>You can use <code>getSelectedItem()<\/code> to get the selected one.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String name[] = {\"One\",\"Two\",\"Three\",\"Four\"};\nJComboBox combo = new JComboBox(name);\ncombo.addItemListener(new ItemListener(){\n   public void itemStateChanged(ItemEvent ie){\n       String str = (String)combo.getSelectedItem();\n       System.out.println(\"Selected Item is: \" + str);\n   }\n});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
